KEY RESPONSIBILITIES

musculoskeletal physiotherapy - treating issues such as strains, sprains, back pain and posture problems;
sports physiotherapy - working to reduce pain and reintroduce range of movement after sports injuries;
rehabilitation and pain management - introducing exercises to reduce and manage pain following surgery, injury or illness;
provide supervision to physiotherapy assistants and co-workers. 

JOB REQUIREMENTS

Degree in Physiotherapy;
Registered with Physiotherapists Board of Hong Kong;
With relevant experience in musculoskeletal and sports rehabilitation is preferred;
Good communication and manual skills;
Able to work as a team member and also Independently;
Independent initiative, with strong sense of responsibility;
Pleasant, out-going, well-organized, highly motivated excellent interpersonal and communication skills                                                                          

We offer attractive package including discretionary bonus and medical insurance to the right candidate. Please apply with full resume stating present & expected salary and date available to: The Human Resources Department by clicking APPLY NOW.

(Personal data collected would be used for recruitment purpose only.)

Duties and Responsibilities:
職責：

Lead an intense and energetic Kickboxing classes; 帶領Kickboxing課程;
Providing adequate warm-up, class content, stretching & cool down; 提供足夠的熱身、課程內容、伸展和放鬆;
Instruction to class participants on effective workout methods while demonstrating proper technique; 向學員講解有效的鍛煉方法，同時展示正確的技術;
Maintaining a positive experience for members and class participants; 為會員和課堂參與者提供積極的體驗;
Motivate members towards participating in Kickboxing classes; 帶動及激勵會員參與
Document student attendance; 記錄學生出勤;
Keep accurate records on student fitness goals and progress. 準確記錄學生健身目標和進度
Requirements and Qualifications:
要求和資格：

Qualified Group Fitness certification/multiple specialized certification; 合格團體健身認證/多項專業認證;
Completion of a 200-hour Kickboxing training course is a plus; 完成200小時瑜Kickboxing練課程者優先
CPR and First Aid certified is an advantage (preferred but is not essential); 心肺復蘇術和急救認證(不是必需的);
1-3 years of Kickboxing instructor experience preferred; 1-3年Kickboxing教練經驗優先
Friendly and outgoing with excellent communication skills; 友善外向，具有良好的溝通技巧
Enthusiasm for personal health and fitness. 熱衷個人健康和健身

THE JOB

Reporting to the Sport Medicine Manager, the Part-time Registered Nurse will be responsible for the following duties:


To assist clinic doctor in medical consultation and performing clinical procedures;
To provide quality nursing care to scholarship athletes: first aid treatment, clinical nursing care, wound management and vaccinations;
 To deliver administration work of the Hong Kong Sports Institute Clinic
To assist clinic doctor in medical screening; and
To perform any other appropriate duties as assigned by supervisor.
THE REQUIREMENTS
Registered Nurse/ Enrolled Nurse (Hong Kong Nursing Council) with a valid practicing certificate;
Minimum of 5 years’ post registration clinical experience for Registered Nurse, Minimum of 8 years post- registration clinical experience for Enrolled Nurse is preferred;
Sports medicine experience (including athletes health care, sports related wound management) is an advantage;
Knowledge of World Anti-Doping Agency’s (WADA) anti-doping regulations and experience is an advantage;
Good command of spoken and written English; Able to communicate in Cantonese and Putonghua is an advantage; and
Awareness/ knowledge of Child Protection in sport and equal opportunity issues in the context of Hong Kong are an added advantage.
 APPLICATIONS
Please send the completed Application Form with indication of expected salary to The Human Resources Manager, Hong Kong Sports Institute Ltd, 25 Yuen Wo Road, Sha Tin, New Territories or email: hrdept @ hksi.org.hk . Please quote reference no. JD-20220106-PTRN in the application.

Appointment will be on a fixed term contract. General information is available at the website http://www.hksi.org.hk.
Applicants who are not invited for interview within six months may consider their applications unsuccessful.
All applications will be treated in the strictest confidence. Data collected will be used for recruitment and other employment-related purposes only.
